<title>USA: LifeTech reorganizes Ludwig Mining.</title>
<headline>LifeTech reorganizes Ludwig Mining.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-06-10</dateline>
<text>
<p>LifeTech Enterprises Inc said it has completed the reorganization of Ludwig Mining Co into the healthcare company, which will retain the name LifeTech Enterprises Inc.</p>
<p>LifeTech will begin trading on the OTC Bulletin Board under Ludwig's old symbol &quot;LWGM&quot; until a new symbol is approved within the next 30 days.</p>
<p>Ludwig Mining was a public corporation that had no substantial assets, liabilities or business operations.</p>
<p>LifeTech provides healthcare products and equipment to the China and other countries in Asia.</p>
